Description           
	
      Scandium is a silvery-white metallic d-block element. It has 
historically been classified as a rare-earth element, together with
yttrium and the lanthanides.Scandium is present in most of the deposits
of rare-earth and uranium compounds.It develops a slightly yellowish or
pinkish cast when oxidized by air.It issusceptible to weathering and 
dissoles slowly in most dilute acids.